member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.KERNELAPICONSTANTS.LZ_FREEFORM
member.summary: Recognition of free forms. The page contains a filled, gridded form, and the best possible OCR accuracy is desired, without creating formatted output. In this case the gridded form is decomposed into smaller text zones optimized for OCR. The zones are not sorted by reading order. It cannot be combined with LZ_FORM. member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_DECOMP.DCM_FAST
member.summary: For non-Asian languages this algorithm can be treated as a simplified variant of DCM_LEGACY: this algorithm does not try to find tables on the page. It is the fastest (but least accurate) parsing algorithm available. Use it only for simple page parsing tasks! For Asian languages this is the same as DCM_LEGACY.

member.summary: The most accurate page parsing module.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_DECOMP.DCM_LEGACY
member.summary: Simple page decomposition. This is faster but less accurate than the standard mode.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_DECOMP.DCM_AUTO
member.summary: Automatic. The Engine will determine at runtime which algorithm will be applied. This depends on the trade-off setting: DCM_LEGACY algorithm is applied when trade-off is TO_FAST and DCM_STANDARD is applied otherwise (Default.)

member.summary: Graphic type zone. This type of zone contains graphics, i.e. this zone will not be recognized at all and all other recognition related settings will be ignored. The only reason to have such a zone is to save or export the image inside it.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.ZONETYPE.WT_TABLE
member.summary: Table type zone. This type means that the zone contains a table, i.e. rows and columns, with or without a grid. Such zones will be handled differently from flowed text type zones. The Engine will try to reconstruct as much of the original table text layout of the zone as the final output document format supports.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.ZONETYPE.WT_FLOW
member.summary: Flowed text. This zone type means that the zone contains textual information arranged horizontally without a table type structure inside. It can also be used for horizontally appearing CJK characters.

member.name: T:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_STRETCHMODE
member.summary: Image stretching mode.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_STRETCHMODE.STRETCH_AVG
member.summary: If the image is B/W, 4-bit grayscale or 8-bit grayscale use 256-level grayscale to combine eliminated pixels. This will result in an output of an 8-bit grayscale bitmap. If the image is palette-color or 24-bit color, use 24-bit color to combine eliminated pixels. This will produce an output of a 24-bit color bitmap. Note, that if the destination rectangle size is greater than the source rectangle size, the color depth of the output bitmap will be the same as the color depth of the input image.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_STRETCHMODE.STRETCH_AND
member.summary: Uses the AND operator to combine eliminated pixels with the remaining ones. This mode preserves white pixels at the expense of black pixels.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_STRETCHMODE.STRETCH_OR
member.summary: Uses the OR operator to combine eliminated pixels with the remaining ones. This mode preserves black pixels at the expense of white pixels. (Assuming that black is coded as 1.)

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_STRETCHMODE.STRETCH_DELETE
member.summary: Deletes eliminated pixels. Information in the eliminated pixels is not preserved (Default).

member.name: T:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.FILLAREA_FLAGS
member.summary: Determining the area to be filled.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.FILLAREA_FLAGS.FILL_FLEXIBLEBPS
member.summary: Increase the color depth of the image if necessary. E.g.: the current image is gray-scale and the filling color is red: if this flag is set the image is changed to 24-bit true-color, if this flag is not set the fillcolor is converted down to gray. This parameter can be combined with FILL_INSIDE or FILL_OUTSIDE.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.FILLAREA_FLAGS.FILL_OUTSIDE
member.summary: Fill the image outside the rectangle.

member.name: T:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_RESENH
member.summary: Image resolution enhancement.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_RESENH.RE_AUTO
member.summary: Resolution enhancement depends on the tradeoff setting: if tradeoff is , RE_LEGACY mode, otherwise RE_STANDARD is used. RE_AUTO is the default setting.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_RESENH.RE_STANDARD
member.summary: The ratio is detected dynamically: it depends on the resolution of the non-BW image and on the detected average character size. Resolution enhancement is not applied above 210 DPI. The mentioned character size detection is performed only during image preprocessing.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_RESENH.RE_LEGACY
member.summary: The ratio of the enhancement depends on the resolution of the non-BW image. The ratio is 2.0 if the resolution is less than or equal to 160 DPI, and it is 1.5 if the resolution is less than or equal to 210 DPI. Otherwise resolution enhancement is not applied (this mode is the same as RE_AUTO in version 12.6).

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_RESENH.RE_YES
member.summary: Forced (unconditional) resolution enhancement. The resolution of the BW image will be the double of the original one (ratio is 2).

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_RESENH.RE_NO
member.summary: Resolution enhancement is disabled.

member.name: T:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_CONVERSION
member.summary: Image conversion types.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_CONVERSION.CNV_GRAY
member.summary: For a color image: a grayscale image is created in the Engine's memory. For B/W or grayscale images: no conversion is performed while loading the image.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_CONVERSION.CNV_GLOBAL
member.summary: This has an effect on grayscale or 24-bit color images: a B/W image is created in the Engine's memory. An automatic thresholding algorithm with a page-level global threshold value is applied in order to binarize the image.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_CONVERSION.CNV_NO
member.summary: There is no conversion while loading the image. The image is loaded into the Engine's memory without any conversion (i.e. a color image retains its color attributes).

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_CONVERSION.CNV_SET
member.summary: This has an effect on grayscale or 24-bit color images: a B/W image is created in the Engine's memory. This setting will implement a user-defined threshold value, defined by the property.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMG_CONVERSION.CNV_AUTO
member.summary: This has an effect on grayscale or 24-bit color images: a B/W image is created in the Engine's memory. An automatic adaptive thresholding algorithm is applied to the image binarization. Use the property to fine-tune the threshold calculation.

member.summary: "OmniPageCSDK" page serialization format. One page format, not appendable. OPG file contains all members of the page including images, zones, letters and other internal information stored by page. Binary images not image-only PDF images and palette-color images are saved using lossless compression, true-color and gray-scale images are saved using lossy compression. Loading an OPG file restores the saved page. Primary image conversion is not applied when OPG file is loaded.

member.summary: Used internally by output converters.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_THUMBNAIL
member.summary: Thumbnail image (miniature color image) generated from the current one. Its creation preserves aspect ratio, but the resulting image has the user-given size. Therefore empty areas may be generated at the top and bottom, or the left and right sides of that image. These empty areas will be filled with a given color called thumbnail color.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_OCR
member.summary: OCR image generated from the BW one by the recognition process. This is a black-and-white image used by the OCR engines. It contains information only inside the zones to be recognized. These zones may be auto-inverted; underlines and graphical elements may be removed from them. The creation method depends on the current page parse, OCR settings and the properties of the zones.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_BW
member.summary: Black-and-white image generated from the current image during preprocessing or implicit secondary image conversion. It can have higher resolution than the current image.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_CURRENT
member.summary: This is the current image. Most functions work on this image. This image always exists. After loading an image it corresponds with the original image. Deskew, rotation, and other image manipulation functions modify this image. To keep compatibility with the previous version CSDK, use II_CURRENT.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_ORIGINAL
member.summary: Original image from scanner or file. It is not conserved unless the 's property is set to True. Deskew, rotation, and other image manipulation functions do not modify this image. By default this image exists until II_CURRENT is generated from it, then it is deleted from the HPAGE.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_BGLAYER
member.summary: Background layer. This image exists only for non-image-only PDF and XPS. It contains the background image without the text layer.

member.name: F:Nuance.OmniPage.CSDK.IproPlus.IMAGEINDEX.II_UNDEFINED
member.summary: Undefined type.
